            <th class="px-3 py-2 text-left font-semibold border-b border-gray-600"><span class="math"> is still generic. In particular a recipient of </span>J(C)<span class="math"> cannot simply check whether </span></th>

            <th class="px-3 py-2 text-left font-semibold border-b border-gray-600">J(C)</th>

            <th class="px-3 py-2 text-left font-semibold border-b border-gray-600">$ is itself smooth, but must know which related Jacobian to check.</th>

          </tr>

        </thead>

